      {
        "instructions": [
          "Rinse the lentils thoroughly in cold water. Soak in cold water until needed.",
          "Heat oil in a large pot or dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
          "Add the onion and saute for 2-3 minutes, stirring, until fragrant.",
          "Lower heat to medium, then add the carrots, celery, garlic, chili flakes, and oregano. Saute 7-8 minutes, stirring.",
          "Add the tomato paste, browning it just a bit in the pan (this will deepen the flavor).",
          "Add the red wine, and cook perhaps most of it off.",
          "Add the chopped, peeled tomatoes and cook them down for just a few minutes.",
          "Add the lentils and vegetable stock (and hemp seeds or walnuts if using).",
          "Bring to a boil and simmer gently for about half an hour (stirring well every now and then as the lentils tend to stick to the bottom).",
          "Optionally continue cooking uncovered until most of the liquid has cooked off.",
          "Serve drizzled with balsamic vinegar and with a generous amount of parmesan and some basil leaves."
